         <abstract>
            <p>There are many practical and effective investment strategies that do not involve the riskless arbitrage concept. The purpose of this paper is to examine the optimal security mix for a portfolio consisting of a single stock, a call option on the stock, and a safe asset. Optimal solutions are analyzed given various assumptions about risk and return characteristics of the stock and prices of options, giving the reader some practical insights into the use of options as a means of improving a stock portfolio's long-run performance.</p>
         </abstract>
